  "text": "Tobacco plants (Nicotiana tabacum var. Blight Yellow 4) were grown in a growth chamber (28 C, 16 h light and 8 h dark) for 4 weeks. Preparation of S30 fractions from intact tobacco chloroplasts and in vitro translation reactions were carried out as previously described [CITATION_1] . The dialyzed S30 fraction ($0.5 ml, $15 mg/ml protein) could be stored at À70",
